NÃ®mes - Rennes: the date of the meeting
Postponed this weekend because of heavy rains, the meeting between NÃ®mes and Rennes will finally take place on Wednesday, January 15, 2020.
06 Nov 2019, 13:48 by Thomas Rassouli



16-year-old Eduardo Camavinga, staggering with Stade Rennais from Steve Mandanda to Memphis Depay, to the young Eduardo Camavinga, several individuals emerged from the lot this weekend, on the occasion of the second day of Ligue 1. Icon Sport Overview

Mandanda, Camavinga, Memphis, ... the typical team of the weekend in Ligue 1




The decision will not have dragged on. A few days after having decided to postpone the game due to heavy rains, the LFP decided to fix the new date of the meeting between the NÃ®mes Olympique and Stade Rennais to Wednesday, January 15, 2020.
For the Stade Rennais, this meeting will take place four days after receiving the Olympique de Marseille at Roazhon Park (11/01), when NÃ®mes will have received the Stade de Reims on the same date.
